Mind the *reefing* use case: keep existing stopper for main sail so that I can do all reefing actions in one place by the mast?
I have to handle the *reefing hook* in place anyway (between mast and boom) so there is no point in relocating the reef lines. For reefing the existing location of main sail's clutch may be perfect.
Also to apply the winch (on the mast) I need to use the existing mast clutch. Could then transfer load to mast-foot-clutch.
